\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces \textbf  {The Stage-Aware Disambiguation paradigm of SADIR.} \textbf  {(a) The Dual Ambiguity Challenge:} Subjective visual intent recognition is fundamentally bottlenecked by \textit  {semantic ambiguity} (highly overlapping conceptual boundaries during inference) and \textit  {supervisory ambiguity} (annotator disagreement and noise during training). \textbf  {(b) Stage-Aware Pipeline:} our SADIR framework introduces a \textit  {stage-aware} paradigm. During training, the model resolves supervisory ambiguity by leveraging VLM-derived commonsense, adaptively gated by annotator agreement. During inference, the model tackles semantic ambiguity by refining predictions within a compact Top-$K$ candidate pool using text priors, with zero extra visual computational overhead.}}{3}{}\protected@file@percent }
\providecommand*\caption@xref[2]{\@setref\relax\@undefined{#1}}
\newlabel{fig:teaser}{{1}{3}{}{figure.1}{}}
