\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces Overview of the SADIR framework. The framework explicitly decouples the disambiguation process into two stages. \textbf  {(Top) Training Stage:} The Uncertainty-guided Text Distillation (UTD) module employs a VLM-derived teacher to generate contrastive textual rationales. The distillation process is adaptively gated by the annotator agreement score $\omega $, balancing objective visual supervision and subjective semantic guidance. \textbf  {(Bottom) Inference Stage:} The Semantic Local Reranking and Calibration (SLR-C) module extracts Top-$K$ candidate intents from the visual logits and refines them using visually-grounded semantic priors, followed by class-wise calibration for the final prediction.}}{8}{}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:sadir_framework}{{2}{8}{}{figure.2}{}}
